The other bill would make it illegal for transgender people to change gender markers on their Idaho birth certificates.
An Idaho Attorney General’s Office’s analysis of the bills, which was provided to lawmakers, found them possibly unconstitutional and open to legal challenge.
The ACLU of Idaho issued a statement saying that it would not hesitate to fight the measures:“The ACLU of Idaho condemns Governor Brad Little’s decision to sign discriminatory, unconstitutional, and deeply hurtful anti-transgender bills into law.
Little vetoed the bill Monday.
Little vetoed this bill on Friday.